1.3 Write your first JSX
At first glance, it looks an awful a lot like HTML, especially the JSX that we have here, since it only uses div, paragraph and other common HTML tags. However, JSX goes 
beyond HTML. We'll see many examples of this throughout the course. 
But one of the first ways this is true is that JSX allows us to use other components we've defined as tags.

Another nice thing about JSX is that it's not a separate thing from JavaScript. What I mean by that is that we can assign JSX expressions to JavaScript variables, 
and then use JavaScript logic to help structure and restructure our pages.
This means that if we wanted to do something like display a different greeting message element on the page, depending on the time of day, 

